cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SE 

The paper discusses active learning algorithms for anomaly detection, which involves machine learning techniques for classification and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) since the paper focuses on applications in computer security and fraud prevention. The paper also discusses algorithms for improving diversity and interpretability, which suggests possible sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses adapting to streaming data settings, which suggests a possible sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
